Bishop’s much loved and much discussed ode to loss, which Claudia Roth Pierpont called “a triumph of control, understatement, wit.
Even of self-mockery, in the poetically pushed rhyme word “vaster,” and the ladylike, pinkies-up “shan’t.”
An exceedingly rare mention of her mother—as a woman who once owned a watch.
A continent standing in for losses larger than itself.”
